/div><div class="t m70b x4a he y15f9 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What did he then tell the Jews? Verses 14, 15. </div><div class="t m249c xe h1 ya5b ff1 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">n. </div><div class="t m6de x18 he y14aa ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What effect did his testimony have on the Jews? Verse i6. </div><div class="t m9a1 x4a he y1027 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Note 4. </div><div class="t m41c xe he y109b ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. </div><div class="t me0 x4a he y154a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">With what statement did Jesus justify His act of healing on </div><div class="t mbe5 x18 he y92d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Sabbath? Verse i7, </div><div class="t m41c xe he ye4c ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">13. </div><div class="t m4b2 x18 he y92e ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did this statement affect the Jews? Why did it have </div><div class="t ma5 x4a he y1179 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">this effect? Verse 18. </div><div class="t m41c xe he y101a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">14. </div><div class="t m165a x4a he y101a ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What relationship did Jesus say exists between Himself </div><div class="t m45a x18 he yec9 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and the Father? Verses 19, zo. </div><div class="t m41c xe he y95d ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">15. </div><div class="t m5ef x4a he yeca ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What had the Father done that the Son might be honored? </div><div class="t m15b x4a he yc05 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Verses 21-23. </div><div class="t m860 x92 he yf39 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">z6. What is said of those who hear Christ&apos;s words, and believe </div><div class="t m5f8 x4a he yd98 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">on the Father who sent Him? Verse 24. </div><div class="t m155e x84 h7b yf40 ff1 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTES </div><div class="t m40c x26 h7b yd40 ff1 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I. </div><div class="t m823 x74 he y1284 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;At certain seasons the waters of this pool were agitated, </div><div class="t m59a xe he yee5 ff4 fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">